column5: William Jourdan Rapp (1895-1942) was a free-lance writer, playwright, radio script writer, and producer. The collection contains correspondence, plays, advertising and article manuscripts, Harlem Renaissance research, biographical material, publications, photographs, and a WWI era scrapbook of a YMCA camp in Greece.|"Jeremiah the Magnificent" A Drama in Three Acts by William Jourdan Rapp and Wallace Thurman
